PARADISHWIDOW BIRD
(steganura paraaisea
A tropical species with a brilliant plumage inhabiting a widespread
area, from the Sudan to Eritrea, southwards to Angola, Damaraland,
Knodesia, botswand, Iransvadi, Fortuguese cast Ainica and Nalal.
They are commonly seen in small flocks searching for seeds on the
ground, perened on top or trees or nyms doout bot in nant or Ol
the ground the broad pointed tail feathers of the male, a neat flier, forms
an impressive sight. The males have a quiet pretty song.
The Paradise Widow Bird is said to be parasitic in its nesting habits.
PARADENNK
moreganura paraaisea
'n Tropiese spesie met skitterende vere wat oor 'n wye gebied aan-
seter word van oe soecan en cutea suewaars tou in Angoa.
Damaraland, Rhodesie, Botswana, Transvaal, Portugees-Oos-Afrika
en Natal.
ronavileg. sower in viug as op ale grond is ale oree, gepunte sterlvere
van die mannetjie, wat goed kan vlieg, 'n indrukwekkende gesig. Die
mannetjies sing sag en mooi.
Daar word beweer dat die paradysvink sy eiertjies deur ander voëls
aat utoroel.
